      "writtenOn": "2020-04-15T21:46:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that\u0027s more of a question for Florin or whoever wants to maintain this code. I just started writing a comment about how 1-1000 would be nice here, but then as I looked at the code I slowly realized that was decidedly non-trivial to do correctly or nicely right here. In the current setup many attributes would probably need to be specialized. At the moment it\u0027s probably much better to create a SkSVGFontWeightValue and have it know how to parse itself (and probably always report itself as a number, since the normal and bold keywords are actually just longhand for the numbers 400 and 700) than to use a SkSVGStringValue and try to parse it later. I really have no idea how to try to support \u0027lighter\u0027 and \u0027heavier\u0027 in the current framework.\n\nEven font-style is now \u0027normal | italic | oblique \u003cangle\u003e?\u0027",
